race.comment: Tricky race. ISLA'S FURY (4) looks a progressive type and comes back in grade after a fair run in a stronger metropolitan race last start. The barrier makes things interesting but you can back in Jake Toeroek to overcome the bother. She can win. BROOKLYN BABY (11) is having her second run for the new stable and can improve. She's better than what she showed last start and, from a good draw, she should have a tactical advantage over several key rivals. LAKE AGAWAM (13) is another that draws well and looks ready to win third-up. He was an eyecatcher at Balaklava last start. The best of BABAYKA (1) puts him right in the picture and he looks well placed back to this grade, while TAKING OMAHA (2) is another worth some thoughts for wider plays.
